<subSubSection id="6D837C85102EFFB1DBB2FD2049102EB0" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="description">
<paragraph id="25262F0E102EFFB1DBB2FD204D7629A8" blockId="11.[151,517,582,645]" box="[151,323,618,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1DBBAFD204CDD29A8" box="[159,232,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Asianthrips species. (1) A. balianus, female (mac). (2) A. bamboosielloides, female (mac). A. bicolor, 3–4; (3) Female (mac); (4) Female (mic). (5) A. borneoensis, female (mac). A. dasycornis, 6–7; (6) Female (mac); (7) Male (mic). A. denticornis, 8–9; (8) Male (mac); (9) Female (mic). (10) A. longior, female (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1DBD1FD214D0E29A8" box="[244,315,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">48–54</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E102EFFB1DBB2FDF84FD82FC4" blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1653]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DBB2FDF84D4229E1" box="[151,375,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body brown (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1D90CFDF84E4429E0" box="[553,625,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Asianthrips species. (1) A. balianus, female (mac). (2) A. bamboosielloides, female (mac). A. bicolor, 3–4; (3) Female (mac); (4) Female (mic). (5) A. borneoensis, female (mac). A. dasycornis, 6–7; (6) Female (mac); (7) Male (mic). A. denticornis, 8–9; (8) Male (mac); (9) Female (mic). (10) A. longior, female (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Antennal segment III yellow, weakly shaded with brown, remaining segments uniformly brown. All femora brown, concolourous with body, with extreme apices yellowish; fore and mid tibiae pale brown to brown, with bases and apices yellow, hind tibiae yellow, shaded with pale brown at middle; all tarsi yellow. Fore wings and body setae almost colourless. Head (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1D8B0FC544FD32814" box="[917,998,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) almost as long as wide; dorsal surface generally sculptured with transverse reticulation. Cheeks very weakly rounded, weakly narrowed to base. Postocular setae much longer than eyes. Postocellar setae longer than a diameter of posterior ocellus. Eyes about 0.4 times as long as head. Antennal segments VII and VIII somewhat broadly fused, segment VIII almost cone-shaped (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1DE4AFCC04C8228E4" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
); segment III with two sense cones. Maxillary stylets retracted into head capsule, but not reaching postocular setae, rather wide apart, wider than 1/3 of the head width apart at the basal collar of head. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1DE1AFC9849A128C0" box="[1343,1428,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) 0.67 times as long as head and 1.95 times as wide as long; pa about 2/3 of the median pronotal length. Metanotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1DB85FB504CC12F18" box="[160,244,1050,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
) polygonally reticulated anteriorly, longitudinally reticulated posteriorly. Prospinasternum rather small. Mesopresternum and mesoeusternum comparatively narrowly fused medially (Fig, 51), with rather long sutures between them at both sides. Fore tarsi unarmed. Fore wings with 4–5 duplicated cilia. Tergites comparatively small (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1DB85FBCC4CC02F8C" box="[160,245,1158,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
), especially tergites III–V somewhat narrow, tergites IV and V almost as wide as pronotum. S1 setae on tergite IX a little longer than S2, 0.86–0.89 times as long as tube, S1 weakly expanded, S2 nearly pointed at apex. Tube 0.63 times as long as head. Anal setae almost as long as tube (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1D8A9FB844FD42FC4" box="[908,993,1230,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,181,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[156,1432,181,1713]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Asianthrips borneoensis, sp. n., female (mac). (48) Head &amp; pronotum; (49) Antenna; (50) Metanotum; (51) Mesopresternum; (52) Pelta; (53) Tergites II–III; (54) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404890/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E102EFFB1DBE2FBB849102EB0" blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1653]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DBE2FBB84D4B2E20" bold="true" box="[199,382,1267,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Measurements.</emphasis>
Female 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC102EFFB1DAC3FBB84E7D2E20" box="[486,584,1267,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">holotype</typeStatus>
in microns. Distended body length 1650. Head length 150, width across cheeks 152. Compound eye dorsal length 59. Pronotum length 100, width 195. Fore wing length about 710. Tube length 95, width across base 50. Antenna length about 340, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 49 (25), 53 (25), 46 (23), 43 (22), 37 (22), 30 (15). Postocular setae 82–85. Pronotal aa about 50, am 44–45, ml 59–63, pa 67–68, epim 63–65. S1 setae on tergite IX 82–85, S2 setae on tergite IX about 80. Anal setae about 100.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
