<subSubSection id="6D837C85102EFFB1DBE2FAA448CC2D58" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E102EFFB1DBE2FAA448CC2D58" blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1653]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DBE2FAA44D0E2D24" bold="true" box="[199,315,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Remarks.</emphasis>
The unique 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC102EFFB1DAE3FAA44E1D2D24" box="[454,552,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">holotype</typeStatus>
female of 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1D9BAFAA44F712D24" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[671,836,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneoensis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1D9BAFAA44F712D24" box="[671,836,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. borneoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected together with 
<specimenCount id="339FE487102EFFB1DFA7FAA4494B2D24" box="[1154,1406,1519,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="female" typeStatus="paratype">three paratype females</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1DBB2F9584D052D00" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,304,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasycornis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DBB2F9584D052D00" box="[151,304,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. dasycornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, newly described below. The antennal segment III of this species has only two sense cones, and this character state is shared with 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1DAC4F97C4EA42D7D" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[481,657,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DAC4F97C4EA42D7D" box="[481,657,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, newly described below. 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1D889F97C48692D7D" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[940,1116,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1D889F97C48692D7D" box="[940,1116,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, has rather slender antennal segment VIII which is distinctly constricted at base and narrowly fused to the segment VII.
